The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 HSBC to use i-flex package

 OUR CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 19: Within seven days of announcing the US-based Wachovia Corporation deal, i-flex solutions Ltd today announced its first ever partnership with the Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Ltd (HSBC). The size of the deal is not known. 

 i-flex solutions said it would implement its Flexcube Investor Services modules as the software solution for the transfer agency and investor services business of HSBCs Institutional Fund Services (IFS) globally. 

 HSBCs Institutional Fund Services (IFS) business will deploy Flexcube with its investor services modules globally, the company said in a release. 

 To begin with, the initial stages of implementation will take place in six countries in Asia and Africa. We will begin with Asia and Africa, and then move on to the other geographies, an i-flex spokesperson said. 




